  "prompt": "How do I delete snapchat conversation without using clear conversations?",
  "response": "If you want to delete a specific Snapchat conversation without using the \"Clear Conversations\" option, you can do so by following these steps:\n\n1. **Open Snapchat**: Launch the Snapchat app on your device.\n\n2. **Go to Chat Screen**: Swipe right on the camera screen to access the Chat screen.\n\n3. **Find the Conversation**: Scroll through your chat list and locate the conversation you want to delete.\n\n4. **Delete the Conversation**: \n   - Long press (or tap and hold) on the conversation you want to delete.\n   - A menu will pop up.\n   - Tap on **\"Delete Chats\"** or **\"Delete\"** (the exact wording may vary).\n\n5. **Confirm Deletion**: If prompted, confirm that you want to delete the conversation.\n\nKeep in mind that deleting a conversation from your chat list does not delete the messages from the other person's chat list. It will only remove the conversation from your view. If you wish to ensure the messages are deleted from both sides, you can ask the other person to delete the conversation as well.",
